The group was moving to the other side of the road to settle on land which has been earmarked for the Alexandra City Project. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Department of Human Settlements has condemned an attempted land invasion in Marlboro, north of Johannesburg.A group of land invaders moving furniture and other household items were dispersed by metro police officers after disrupting traffic on the N3 highway.The group was moving to the other side of the road to settle on land which has been earmarked for the Alexandra City Project.The department s Keith Khoza says land invasions impact government efforts to respond to the housing needs of the poor. These actions are calculated to sabotage and undermine development. It is spearheaded by people who are not committed to ensuring that government would speed up development. 